        'job' => [
            'model' => 'job',
            'usesRefTable' => true
        ]
    ];
}




Optionally you can of course combine this with the previously talked about
"relTable" option to specify the name of the relation table if the default naming
doesn't work for you.


Namespaces


Just a quick explanation of namespaces in the model definition...


When defining related models in your $model_attributes array, namespaces are
always absolute, never relative. See the namespaced Notes model below and the
relationship definition added to User for an example:


