relationship (which in this example would be another User) and use the LoadMap embedded there as 
the mapping for any model(s) fetched for that relationship.


The 
'Job' => new LoadMap()
 section is the 2nd argument to the 
madeBy
 LoadMap in the same way 
that 
madeBy
 is the 2nd argument to the root level LoadMap. What this means is that when the 

madeBy
 User model is fetched, the Job relationship on that model should also be loaded and the 
job name and ID should be mapped using the embedded loadMap there.


Finally the 3rd and 4th arguments are the onLoad function and variables for the root level User models.




